  "course_description": "For first-year students only. Entry level seminar focusing on a specific topic. May be repeated for credit when topic varies.",
  "course_notes": "This freshman seminar is an AI-integrated introduction to the three most important approaches to mathematical modeling in political science: (1) statistical modeling, (2) systems modeling, and (3) rational choice / game theory modeling. Students will learn how mathematical approaches are employed in the social sciences by connecting those approaches to contemporary news stories. AI is used to help brainstorm about such connections. Students are not required to solve any mathematics in the course. There are no prerequisites. The class grades are based on regular writing assignments, presentations, and attendance. There are no tests.",
